==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hopperdozer
<hw>Hop"per*doz`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hopper</ets> (as in grass<ets>hopper</ets>) + <ets>doze</ets>
or <ets>dose</ets>; because conceived as putting insects to sleep or as
dosing them with poison.]</ety> <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>An appliance
for the destruction of insects, consisting of a shallow iron box,
containing kerosene or coated with tar or other sticky substance, which
may be mounted on wheels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

